# Fixture: fm10-service-nesting
# Finding: SERVICE nesting — federated query inside outer SERVICE
# Spec: SPARQL 1.1 Federated Query §4 (SERVICE evaluation)
#
# Hypothesis: A SERVICE pattern may legally appear nested inside another
# SERVICE block. Parsers that forbid SERVICE nesting at the grammar level
# will reject this as a parse error; those that allow unlimited nesting
# accept it. The outer/inner IRI binding and variable scoping must both
# be preserved. This surfaces both accept/reject splits (FM category) and
# variable-scoping disagreements in implementations that do accept it.
#
# Divergence: Grammar-level accept/reject split on nested SERVICE.
# Some parsers reject on depth limit; correct grammar has no such limit.
# Grammar-level behaviour: should parse successfully per spec.

SELECT * WHERE {
  SERVICE <http://endpoint.example/outer> {
    ?s <http://example/p> ?o .
    SERVICE <http://endpoint.example/inner> {
      ?o <http://example/q> ?z .
    }
  }
}
